<paragraph blockId="12.[136,1452,158,1085]" pageId="12" pageNumber="149">
Notes:—Our specimens identified as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boedijn, Sydowia" authorityYear="1951" baseAuthorityName="Berk. &amp; Broome" baseAuthorityYear="1873" box="[612,771,771,796]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Boletinellaceae" genus="Phlebopus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Boletales" pageId="12" pageNumber="149" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="portentosus">
<emphasis box="[612,771,771,796]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="149">P. portentosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are well characterized by a large fruitbody with a yellowish brown, brown, dark brown pileus, a brown, brownish black stipe, a light yellow context sometimes bluing when injured, broadly ellipsoid basidiospores, terminal cells of pileipellis mostly subfusiform or fusiform, and a distribution in tropical Asia. The morphological features of the Chinese collections match well with those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boedijn, Sydowia" authorityYear="1951" baseAuthorityName="Berk. &amp; Broome" baseAuthorityYear="1873" box="[1230,1389,879,904]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Boletinellaceae" genus="Phlebopus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Boletales" pageId="12" pageNumber="149" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="portentosus">
<emphasis box="[1230,1389,879,904]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="149">P. portentosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[136,246,914,940]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="12" pageNumber="149">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pegler, D. N." box="[260,400,914,941]" pageId="12" pageNumber="149" pagination="1 - 519" refId="ref10844" refString="Pegler, D. N. (1986) Agaric flora of Sri Lanka. Kew Bulletin Additional Series 12: 1 - 519." type="book chapter" year="1986">Pegler 1986</bibRefCitation>
), except that the cystidia were not observed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pegler, D. N." box="[929,1082,914,941]" pageId="12" pageNumber="149" pagination="1 - 519" refId="ref10844" refString="Pegler, D. N. (1986) Agaric flora of Sri Lanka. Kew Bulletin Additional Series 12: 1 - 519." type="book chapter" year="1986">Pegler (1986)</bibRefCitation>
whereas they are common in the Chinese specimens (
<figureCitation box="[365,475,950,977]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="13.[136,229,1912,1934]" captionTargetBox="[172,1407,239,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-18@13.[151,1436,187,1885]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 6. Microscopicfeatures of Phlebopus portentosus(FHMU5934).a.Basidia.b. Basidiospores.c. Cheilocystidia.d.Pleurocystidia. e. Pileipellis. f. Stipitipellis. Bars = 10 μm. Drawings by H.J. Xie." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5508821" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5508821/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="149">Fig. 6c, d</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[136,1452,158,1085]" pageId="12" pageNumber="149">
Morphologically, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boedijn, Sydowia" authorityYear="1951" baseAuthorityName="Berk. &amp; Broome" baseAuthorityYear="1873" box="[388,545,987,1012]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Boletinellaceae" genus="Phlebopus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Boletales" pageId="12" pageNumber="149" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="portentosus">
<emphasis box="[388,545,987,1012]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="149">P. portentosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[740,838,987,1012]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Boletinellaceae" genus="Phlebopus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Boletales" pageId="12" pageNumber="149" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="roseus">
<emphasis box="[740,838,987,1012]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="149">P. roseus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a species originally described from Sichuang Province of southwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[321,392,1022,1048]" name="China" pageId="12" pageNumber="149">China</collectingCountry>
. However, 
<taxonomicName box="[518,617,1023,1048]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Boletinellaceae" genus="Phlebopus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Boletales" pageId="12" pageNumber="149" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="roseus">
<emphasis box="[518,617,1023,1048]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="149">P. roseus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a rose pink to reddish stipe, tubular hymenophore with nested angular pores of multiple sizes, and a distribution in subtropical 
<collectingCountry box="[766,833,1058,1084]" name="China" pageId="12" pageNumber="149">China</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Mei, Y. &amp; Liu, C. Y. &amp; Li, S. H. &amp; Guerin-Laguette, A. &amp; Xiao, Y. J. &amp; Tang, P. &amp; Wan, S. P. &amp; Bonito, G. &amp; Wang, Y." box="[848,1025,1058,1085]" pageId="12" pageNumber="149" pagination="1 - 10" refId="ref10446" refString="Mei, Y., Liu, C. Y., Li, S. H., Guerin-Laguette, A., Xiao, Y. J., Tang, P., Wan, S. P., Bonito, G. &amp; Wang, Y. (2020) Phlebopus roseus, a new edible bolete from China, is associated with insects and plants. Mycologia 113: 1 - 10. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00275514.2020.1816781" type="journal article" year="2020">
Mei 
<emphasis box="[901,950,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="149">et al</emphasis>
. 2020
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
